This paper is about sentiment analysis, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper proposes a new framework for open-domain targeted sentiment analysis, which involves extracting opinion targets and their corresponding polarities from a sentence. This task involves machine learning and classification, which are also relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of different models and approaches, which could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE).
